 designed to modify it, and tests should catch those issues. I'm wondering if directly setting a final static field to null could lead to failures later when the ReflectionUtils object interacts with a Scala object. This isn't the target I want, though.\\n\\n**Considering Java support**\\n\\nI’m thinking we might need to support Java versions below 17, which we haven't done yet. Should we add a test that reaches the `setFinalStatic17Minus` call sites without using direct reflection? Maybe we could adjust `java.version` prior to initializing the `ReflectionUtils` object, but that seems tricky. Our `listToTuple` test accesses the object before setting the version. I'm not sure if test order is guaranteed. We could add a separate test, but is it really necessary? I need to check the git diff.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_048a9df48b4ddf110169fb258d2a3481a1927bcb98f3b062e8\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-yWZLzaDHUuMmmA8ljJHvUgK0n43qN1MUJOMVeemfF9iOMQYTndCgr-UB4MKRo64Sy_uI1iVBjYJun0aDMu-h2_p4PUC3XCO7s5cwHTKC2bKrQVSL9_NzXsf3FxIf-h2unrfXzrkmabfjKdvggZWtsU7R0h4TXYJ0vOePTIiomTckpp_XHIMYmka02E1GYNpyy3iQ1HXR1w8mst-9R7_zb1BAfyPhLrUAB5m4R1nxBGQItiWDlUASa5_JJb6ltjusMawmp2sNkkmN9hWKmv1r__WhJkR4xC96YKQBeJ5OB_x2_NUjOPOJI6zh6nE-FqoYegK0FAbtY-r-CEHt8PXq-Eqm4F7a6VkKVsu3Vk6Kqay5Dd86u__fm5ap9GX1uprp7QrxM_2AvYq9ASNJSYohdvyqirsPumr0gC3HderGAUonGT9xcxMDYvX4sxkwovQF324VPXTa_BVFUgvjhO59vT0P2Zg5397Ir2tO26YaUe6LwOic8kc4nQdCgGAcfaS2k0k-6VYIXdRYyWIZlffE1jPtGqwQWXMC6Iamug9qxXc6XmRVzA64_xlghWQtcKWOmED6O3XzQUMcO_rU0ukhjCdXb1Udtc28VhqbTlsC9KBW3_WVoUit3ai354gyjTYspLnm2rVBz7H-P8U9h2C9B_ryX94Vw0YlxQKudyChhM4KCpz6l_XaiJYK8lZqIToCQp889e52dGh97wUmQolcK0k_30_sSqlUBWbzYu5ijspaL8NFhkBB0OwPXqV8Vr-s3_rnwhpNdy-bBAlMmfqMaCuz2sK_t7G1WkmZA4bY_f2e8Pnv3nmEW7JMpK1qN6HdvZujL6yCPqbC13IDKs0_AaWANumTgsXtA2h6aotVmoaMu5OgsfMpZm6ckAst-tDTPQKrXV2Z-Q0BDeMpxSzrW2CHJlDaTu-LfuqhkYE9k_TPNoQEIxuR1z0QIzTB4gwAoHyfdUdmqTVi6HyXy2aDDW3FsDWZNnT3BSqwnB_iSyrXQYzVcPR351e3wXXlBNhYCmt